          </svg>
          View Code on GitHub
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Text content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg">

        <p>
          <strong>Pure C Server</strong> is a monolithic REST server written entirely
          in C, without relying on any external framework or runtime.
          The project focuses on performance, predictability and a deep understanding
          of low-level networking.
        </p>

        <h2>Design Goals</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>No frameworks, no abstractions</li>
          <li>Full control over memory and execution flow</li>
          <li>Simple and explicit request/response lifecycle</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Architecture</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Monolithic binary</li>
          <li>Single entry point</li>
          <li>Manual routing based on HTTP method and path</li>
          <li>Explicit request parsing and response serialization</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Implemented Features</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>HTTP/1.1 request parsing</li>
          <li>REST-style endpoints</li>
          <li>JSON responses</li>
          <li>Basic concurrency handling</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>C (C17)</li>
          <li>Windows sockets</li>
          <li>Manual memory management</li>
          <li>Zero external dependencies</li>
        </ul>

      </div>

    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>